Jul 19 2010 - 1.0.4
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    8899e78 Bumping versions for 1.0.4 (stable)
    

Jul 08 2010 - 1.0.3
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    0166341 always quote my.cnf values when generating an options file
    de444b6 make sure syntax errors in config files are handled cleanly
    f72d4c7 don't explicitly copy my.cnf or error log to backup directory, as 
            they are included in the tar archive.
    0b7d469 add more logging at each stage of the snapshot lifecycle
    99b8828 ensure snapshot-mountpoint is always cleaned up if it was a 
            tempdir
    01da389 use --defaults-file rather than --defaults-extra-file when setting 
            up bootstrap mysqld
    9d65155 [GH #34] Added scripts/make_release.py to generate a source 
            distribution
    f5182f4 [GH #50] build_rpms.py now works with a normal source distribution
    2d236e3 [GH #51] Update debs to latest holland release
    94e9089 adding holland-xtrabackup subpackage to debian/
    b26809e [GH #49] Include skip-relay-log-index during mysql-lvm mysqld 
            bootstrapping
    94ad2de don't use scope when checking status for mysql 4.1
    f8fb990 log keyboard interrupts a little more cleanly
    dbe8ebf cleanup logging messages to be more clear when a backup fails
    c6d6d64 handle stop-slave with an invalid mysqldump cmd more gracefully
    571e67e allow mysql-binpath to accept both a directory and a path
    280f3c8 skip stop/start slave when running in dry-run mode
    6d1c62d always error early if bin-log-position is requested, but binary 
            logging is not enabled on server
    6e829e2 exit early if stop-slave is requested, but the slave is not 
            running
    5c3d258 record 'show slave status' when stop-slave is enabled
    2d4bb3a fix quoting of my.cnf port values
    fd611f5 ensure dry-run doesn't generate empty savesets
    ae0d409 [GH #45] Handle unreadable databases gracefully
    6286cb1 [GH #44] Resolve spurious 'Bad file descriptor' message when 
            running mysqldump provider in --dry-run mode
    97d8e31 Adding scripts/version_bump.sh for quick version changes
    5f95022 [dev] Version bumped to 1.0.3 (dev)


Jul 08 2010 - 1.0.2 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	b2c02ab Changed purge policy on default.conf
    0529ef8 Resolve GH#43 scripts/build_rpms.py option parsing broken
    d66f10d handle compression errors a bit more gracefully
    77551cf ensure errors in compression are caught and handled appropriately
    577903e be more aggressive about recycling compression processes
    1368ab2 only run purge operations if a backup was successful
    256dac3 report mysql connect error slightly better
    6044fde never purge current backup
    7d79114 never interpolate config files that holland parses
    0b18780 don't write excluded databases to manifest
    1e94ff2 ensure a zero-byte estimated-size is handled gracefully
    1d4dd83 ensure spool is always setup prior to running backup()
    596bc9d ensure bare table names in filters are treated as '*.<name>'
    4087120 [GH #42] Ensure single-quoted my.cnf values are handled correctly
    312b3a5 fix incorrect import in mysqldump-lvm
    f744b44 [GH #41] Ensure views are always treated as transactional when
            deciding whether to use --single-transaction
    7a74dca [GH #40] ensure passwords read from a password-file are always 
            quoted
    3bce689 make basic snapshot framework consistent between mysql-lvm and
            mysqldump-lvm
    4ba075b [GH #39] mysql-lvm now parses snapshot-size without units as 
            megabytes
    9bd1d6c [GH #38] Snapshot callbacks are now sorted in a python-2.3 
            compatible way
    22299ec parse snapshot-size without units as megabytes not bytes
    9d481fd handle broken tables and views in MySQLClient more gracefully
    fc8bc88 only import mysqldump plugin in mysql_lvm when specifically needed
    69af0a5 catch the right exception when mysql-lvm fails to find a logical
            volume
    
    
